description:
Kenneth Wapnick - Journey Through the Workbook of A Course in Miracles (Foundation for A Course in Miracles, 2005). 1711 pp.

This is a detailed commentary on each daily lesson in the Workbook of A Course in Miracles.

As far as I know, there is no official digital version of Ken's Workbook commentary, but apparently someone did a nice job turning the text into pdf files -- one for each lesson. I found them online and combined them all into single pdf file. It's not a scan, so the pages don't match the pagination of the print volumes. Also, Ken's introduction is missing. Otherwise I believe it's all there.

This isn't a beginner's book on ACIM. But for committed Course students, it's a goldmine.


description (refers to print edition):

This eight-volume set is the product of a series of 58 classes conducted at our Foundation's former location in New York. The classes consisted of a line-by-line analysis of the lessons, introductions, reviews, summaries, and the Epilogue. The original discussion has been enlarged considerably, and many additional references included to other relevant portions of the Course, the Preface, the two pamphlets, poems from The Gifts of God, and the prose poem &quot;The Gifts of God.&quot; This work can thus be seen as a complete Course companion to accompany students on their own journey through the workbook.

